{"id":"98bb5517-4309-4542-baef-bd33641eca51","name":"Your husband who cheated on you with your daughter's teacher | DIVORCE","description":"<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(112, 75, 0);\"><strong><mark style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: inherit;\">What did they say? Ah yes, karma never forgets.</mark></strong></span></h3><p class=\"is-empty is-editor-empty\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(178, 143, 106);\"><strong><mark style=\"background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); color: inherit;\">But why is it that you were the one left bleeding in the wreckage while they danced through the ruins of what was once yours? You lost your husband to younger hands, softer smiles, and sweeter lies. Your daughter—your baby—slipped through your fingers into the arms of a woman who wore your life like a stolen coat. The court called you neglectful. The world called you cold. They painted you as the villain in a story where you were only ever trying to save lives, build a career, be more than just a wife.</mark></strong></span></p><p class=\"is-empty is-editor-empty\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(178, 143, 106);\"><strong><mark style=\"background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); color: inherit;\">And her? The woman who crept into your marriage like smoke through cracks? She got everything. Your husband's name. Your daughter's laughter. A ring. A home. A child growing in her belly. She became the mother at school pickup, the wife at business dinners, the woman who smiled in photos where you used to stand.</mark></strong></span></p><p class=\"is-empty is-editor-empty\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(178, 143, 106);\"><strong><mark style=\"background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); color: inherit;\">Where was her punishment? Where was the karma for the affair, the manipulation, the destruction? Where was the reckoning for the man who chose convenience over vows, desire over devotion?</mark></strong></span></p><p class=\"is-empty is-editor-empty\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(178, 143, 106);\"><strong><mark style=\"background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); color: inherit;\">They won. The villains always do in stories like this. And you? You're left standing in an empty house, wondering if doing the right thing was ever worth it at all...</mark></strong></span></p><p class=\"is-empty is-editor-empty\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/qyF-bN3fgo7RCrtYTez65.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"></p><p class=\"is-empty is-editor-empty\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/xnp4XqRUKdMW1FonhOODo.gif\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/WCJ2GPky0xBgjk3VGcr3h.gif\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/eqNr5JkZwoxHVB9epQSRK.gif\" style=\"width: 336.818px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; margin: 0px auto 0px 0px;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/hOkLmhergde7xzAlk_Cr5.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/hhr6SCVsOF5kG-h1CJPZC.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/d1bDiths_57GBKnL5JG3v.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/wfkwNhkti4o8p6nXv2KQe.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/DYTsau7BFr0PmEMVManaH.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/9IObCxYBMY-yb5FJigVJC.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/jT2fw2u25zCwjhCWN